{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6151e8637913fdef662816b6", "type": "numerical", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "94", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A glass rod of rectangular cross-section is bent into the shape shown in the figure below. A parallel beam of light falls perpendicularly on the flat surface <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>. Determine the minimum value of the ratio&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac bevelled=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfrac></math> for which all light entering the glass through surface&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> will emerge from the glass through the surface <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>. The index of refraction of the glass is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.<br />\r<br />\r<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/Q_8412.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%; object-fit:contain\" />", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "2", "solution": {"text": "Consider the representative rays shown in diagram (b). A ray entering the glass through surface A and passing along the inner side of the rod will be reflected by the outer side with the smallest angle <math> <mrow> <mi>\u03b1</mi> </mrow> </math>, at which the reflected ray is tangent to the inner side. We have to consider the conditions under which the ray will undergo total internal reflection before reaching B.<br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/Q_84_soln.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%; object-fit:contain\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 211px;\" /><br /><br />If <math> <mrow> <mi>\u03b1</mi> <mo>&gt;</mo> <msub> <mi>\u03b8</mi> <mtext>c</mtext> </msub> </mrow> </math>, the critical angle, at which total internal reflection occurs, all the incident beam will emerge through the surface B. Hence we require<br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mtext>sin</mtext> <mi>\u03b1</mi> <mo>&gt;</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>n</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br /><br />The geometry gives <math> <mrow> <mtext>sin</mtext> <mi>\u03b1</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>R</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mtext>R</mtext> <mo>+</mo> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br /><br />Therefore <math> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>R</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>R</mtext> <mo>+</mo> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>n</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math>,<br /><br />or <math> <mrow> <msub> <mrow> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>R</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> <mtext>min</mtext> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>n</mtext> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>1.5</mtext> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb581812137319